{"lemma":"تَحْتِ","slug":"تَحْتِ","root":"ت.ح.ت","root_slug":"ت-ح-ت","root_link":"/words/roots/ت-ح-ت","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"تَحْتِ","root":"تحت","pos":"N","occurrence_count":51},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adv","prep"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n3787"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AA%D9%8E%D8%AD%D9%92%D8%AA%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adv","gloss":"below"},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"under","examples":[{"text":"جَلَسْتُ تَحْتَ شَجَرَةِ ٱلزَّيْتُونِ وَٱسْتَمْتَعْتُ بِنَسِيمِ ٱلْهَوَاءِ ٱلْعَلِيلِ.","english":"I sat under the olive tree and enjoyed the gentle breeze."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Originally a case form of a defective noun تَحْت (taḥt, “location that is below”); see the usage note. From the root ت ح ت (t ḥ t). Related to Hebrew תַּחַת, Ge'ez ታሕት (taḥt), Ugaritic 𐎚𐎈𐎚 (tḥt /⁠taḥta⁠/) and Classical Syriac ܬܰܚܬ.\n\nAdverbial accusative of تَحْت (taḥt, “location that is below”). Related to Hebrew תַּחַת (tákhat)."},"ipa":["/taħ.tu/","/ˈtɐħət/","/taħ.ta/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n3787","headword_ar":"تَحْت","root":"tHt","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fawoq","text_ar":"فَوْق"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb, K:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~aHotu","text_ar":"التَّحْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The location that is beneath, below,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"under,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is opposed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfawoqu","text_ar":"الفَوْقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and is used in relation to that which is separate from another thing;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^asofalu","text_ar":"الاَسْفَلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being used in relation to that which is united with [or a part of] another thing. (Kull.) Sometimes, (K,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHot","text_ar":"تَحْت"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an adv. n., (Msb, K,) having a vague signification, its meaning not being clear unless it is prefixed to another word, as in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA taHota h`*aA","text_ar":"هٰذَا تَحْتَ هٰذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is beneath, below,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"under, this"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) And sometimes, it is a simple noun; (K;) in which case, [not having the article"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":",] it is indecl., with dammeh for its termination, (K, and I'Ak p. 204,) provided that the noun to which it should be prefixed is suppressed, and the meaning of this is intended to be understood, but not the word itself; (I'Ak ubi suprà;) as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino taHotu","text_ar":"مِنْ تَحْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Beneath, below,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"under"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (K;) and in the saying,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A^aqabN mino taHotu EariyDN mino Ealu"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Lean beneath; broad above"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: otherwise, it is decl.; (I'Ak ibid.;) as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tajoriy mino taHotihaA AlA^anohaAru","text_ar":"تَجْرِي مِنْ تَحْتِهَا الاَنْهَارُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rivers running beneath them"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (Kur ii. 23, &c.;) i.e., beneath their trees, (Bd, Jel,) and their pavilions. (Jel.) [You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN taHota A^amori","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ تَحْتَ اَمْرِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnK","text_ar":"فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is under the command, rule,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"authority, of such a one."},{"kind":"text","text":"And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN taHotahu fulaAnapu","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ تَحْتَهُ فُلَانَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one has as his wife such a woman:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see an ex. in a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_i*aA","text_ar":"اـِذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":". The dim. is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tuHayot","text_ar":"تُحَيْت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`daA tuHayota h`*aA","text_ar":"هٰدَا تُحَيْتَ هٰذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino tuHayoti","text_ar":"مِنْ تُحَيْتِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA","text_ar":"هٰذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is a little beneath, below,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"under, this."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~aHotu","text_ar":"التَّحْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also the sing. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~uHuwtu","text_ar":"التُّحُوتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAth, TA,) which latter [in the CK erroneously written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~uHutu","text_ar":"التُّحُتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The low, base, vile,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ignoble, persons."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, IAth, K.) It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA taquwmu Als~aAEapu Hat~aY taZohara Alt~uHuwtu wa taholika","text_ar":"لَا تَقُومُ السَّاعَةُ حَتَّى تَظْهَرَ التُّحُوتُ وَ تَهْلِكَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlwuEuwlu","text_ar":"الوُعُولُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The hour"},{"kind":"text","text":"of resurrection"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"will not come until"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the low,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ignoble, persons"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shall prevail"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the noble persons"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shall perish"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (A, IAth, TA:) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"until the treasures that are beneath the earth appear."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And in another trad. it is said that among the signs of the resurrection shall be this:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ano yaEoluw","text_ar":"اَنْ يَعْلُو"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~uHuwtu AlwuEuwla","text_ar":"التُّحُوتُ الوُعُولَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That the weak of mankind shall have ascendency over the strong."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","K","Bd","Jel","IAth","TA","A"]}]}}